
String:
======

1. Write a program to print the given string in reverse order. (Note: use charAt() method)
String company="XTGLOBAL";

2. Write a program for the following scenario.
String companyName="XTGLOBAL INFOTECH LIMITED";
i. Print the total number of characters in the string
ii. Combine two strings and print it on the console.
iii. Print the character at the index 3.

3. Write a program to remove all special characters in the string.
String value="10:35:40 12-20-1234"
output: 10354012201234

3. Write a program to split the string with comma separator and print all string elements on the console.
String countries="India,South Africa,Australia,China,Pakistan,USA";

4. Write a program to retrieve the numbers from the given string and print them on the console.
String message="There are only 3 items available which costs Rs.200/- each.
output:
3
200

5. Write a program to print each word in the given string in reverse order.
String message="India is my country";
output: aidnI si ym yrtnuoc 

